attribute.name: type
attribute.description: The type (class) of the message that the annotated method wishes to receive. If omitted the type will be deduced from the method parameter.

attribute.name: messageProperties
attribute.description: If specified not the message itself will be passed to the method, but instead the listed properties of the message as method parameters.

attribute.name: selector
attribute.description: An selector value for filtering in addition to message selection by type. See 6.11 Using Selectors.

attribute.name: scope
attribute.description: The scope from which the message should be received. The default is the global scope.

attribute.name: order
attribute.description: The order in which handlers should be invoked. The default value is int.MAX_VALUE.

attribute.name: method
attribute.description: The method the message instance should be passed to. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.name: id
attribute.description: Specifies the id of the object to inject, if omitted injection by type is performed.

attribute.name: required
attribute.description: Indicates whether the dependency is required, default if omitted: true.

attribute.name: completeEvent
attribute.description: The event type signalling that the object is fully initialized. Default Event.COMPLETE.

attribute.name: errorEvent
attribute.description: The event type signalling that the object failed to initialize correctly. Default ErrorEvent.ERROR.

attribute.name: method
attribute.description: The name of the method to invoke when the object is fully initialized. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.name: method
attribute.description: The name of the method that produces the obejcts. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.description: The name of the method to invoke when the object is fully initialized. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

metatag.name: Internal
metatag.description: Parsley - May be placed on properties in an AS3 Configuration Class that should not be included in the IOC Container.

attribute.name: names
attribute.description: The names (types) of the events dispatched from the annotated object that the container should manage.

attribute.name: scope
attribute.description: The scope through which the event should be dispatched. If this attribute is omitted the event will be dispatched through all scopes associated with the Context the dispatching object lives in.

attribute.name: type
attribute.description: The type (class) of the message that the annotated property should be bound to.

attribute.name: messageProperty
attribute.description: The name of the property of the message class whose value should be bound to the targetProperty.

attribute.name: selector
attribute.description: An selector value for filtering in addition to message selection by type. See 5.9 Using Selectors.

attribute.name: scope
attribute.description: The scope from which the message should be received. The default is the global scope.

attribute.name: targetProperty
attribute.description: The name of the property that the message property value should be bound to. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.name: property
attribute.description: The property the injected dispatcher function should be injected into. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.name: scope
attribute.description: The scope through which the message should be dispatched. If this attribute is omitted the message will be dispatched through all scopes associated with the Context the dispatching object lives in.

attribute.name: type
attribute.description: The type (class) of the message that was passed to the handler or interceptor that threw an Error. If omitted the error handler applies to all message types.

attribute.name: selector
attribute.description: An selector value for filtering in addition to message selection by type. See 5.9 Using Selectors.

attribute.name: scope
attribute.description: The scope from which the message was dispatched to the handler or interceptor that threw an Error. The default is the global scope.

attribute.description: The interceptor method. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.name: lazy
attribute.description: When set to false (default) the object will be instantiated when the container initializes (but only if the singleton attribute keeps the default value (true). When set to true the object will be instantiated on demand.

attribute.name: singleton
attribute.description: When set to true (default) the container will only create a single instance of the object, cache it internally and return the same instance upon each request. When set to false it will create a new instance upon each request.

attribute.name: id
attribute.description: The id the object should be registered with. If omitted the name of the property that produces (or holds) the object will be used as the id.

attribute.name: order
attribute.description: The initialization order. Only considered for non-lazy singletons, processed in ascending order. Default int.MAX_VALUE.

attribute.name: bundle
attribute.description: The bundle name of the resource.

attribute.name: key
attribute.description: The resource key.

attribute.name: property
attribute.description: The name of the property that the resource should be bound to. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.name: objectId
attribute.description: The id the property value is published with.

attribute.name: scope
attribute.description: The scope the property value is published to.

attribute.name: managed
attribute.description: Indicates whether the value published by this property should be added to the Context (turned into a managed object) while being published.

attribute.name: changeEvent
attribute.description: The event that signals that the property value has changed. Default is change. Not needed in Flex applications where this feature relies on the Flex Binding facility.

attribute.name: property
attribute.description: The name of the property that holds the value to publish. Will be automatically set when used as a Metadata Tag.

attribute.name: objectId
attribute.description: The id the source is published with.

attribute.name: scope
attribute.description: The scope the binding listens to.
